{
  "number": 730,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/730",
  "title": "render calls order is bad when urlSync is used",
  "body": "I managed to break the render calls result order.\n\nUsing the standard dev app on develop, by typing \"mp3\" (fast), you can manage to have results for the query \"mp\".\n\nThis is linked to the url-sync feature since without it it works well.\n\nWhat I did is add a \"render\" method to the search box widget and console.log inside it. Render calls and the query are bad given the current search box value.\n\nIt seems the url sync is re-triggering a search somewhere?\n\nAny idea welcomed, this is linked with #729 because a naive approach with flags to solve #729 can't work if the render call order is not good.\n\n![bug2](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/123822/11692253/f0e97950-9e9e-11e5-819a-5ea0ec826bf6.gif)\n",
